{
  "doc_id": "9828",
  "text": "Possible side effects of Htx and of assist device therapy are neurological events. [CITATION_1] The implantation of an assist device or a Htx requires the use of a cardiopulmonary bypass, with known potential risks for embolic stroke. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Further, during assist device therapy, a strict anticoagulation protocol must be carried out. This leads to an increased risk for anticoagulation drug-associated complications. These can manifest as acute bleeding, stroke, and further neurological dysfunction.",
